3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a new paladin?</span><hr size=1> Flash of Light and your stuns are you for the first 30 levels, from 9 onwards.  Get Cease and Desist from Shadowhaven.  They will form a bank of three stuns with the actual Stun that allow you to absolutely shut down casting mobs.  Flash of Light = agro for mana.  Very low mana cost, and very high agro generation.  I use it as much as all of my stuns combined, if not more.  It's also a fear, back away from a flashed mob and they will run in a straight line in the opposite direction to you.  Best used in open areas, not a good idea indoors *grins*<br><br>Surviving your first nine levels is a bit like being a weaker warrior, you've got to be careful.  Level up your 2HS and 1HS, they are your epic skills.  Everything else is up to RP/gameplay considerations (I never bothered, and I don't regret it to be honest, Ghoulbane and Soulfire do me perfectly fine).  Fear kite undead, mummies in the Desert of Ro are your best bet for this at low levels.  Lots of space, not populated, and easy to run from if something goes wrong.  Don't bother with your undead DD spells unless you really want to show off.  They're crap.  They come in handy sometimes, for pulling, but only if you want that little bit of damage advantage.  Also, forget being able to play a healer until 30 at least.  Good at downtime healing, but healing during fighting is a bad idea.  <br><br>Advice?  Collect bone chips are every opportunity.  Give in to people for every guild other than the Deepwater Knights.  Build up faction.  Faction is the bane of a paladin's life, it's required for EVERYTHING.  If it's not built up in your youth, you will regret it later.  Kill the heretic on the docks in Tox forest every chance you get.  That'll fix your Deepwater faction over time.  Give in maybe 2pp's worth of 2gps everytime you see Lashun Novashine.  That will save you a lot of pain in the future.  Get your Ghoulbane.  That sword will save you even more pain than giving 2gps to Novashine will.  Do the Testiment of Truth quest in the Hall of Truth at the first opportunity.  That will save you a bit of heartache (it's TLC past 13th I think).<br><br>Unrest and Befallen will be your haunts (no pun intended), especially once you wield Ghoulbane *smiles*<br><br>Oh, and poke me sometime.  Welcome to the fold *smiles*<br><br>**<br>There's nothing elsewhere to be perfectly honest that will disagree on anything but minor details.  Some paladins like FoL for agro, other's swear by stuns.  I used FoL mostly and stuns for interrupting casting at precise moments.  However, Paladins of Norrath is a good place to start if you want anything more extensive.  I've been as brief as I can.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>** <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A> at: 8/19/02 8:28:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uyethuy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yethuy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 7:21:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a new paladin?</span><hr size=1>    I have been hearing some good advice so far I would like to also add what I feel is the most important aide of the pally.  Know who is in your group and know where they are in your F keys so you can LoH if needed.  I (in another incarnation) usually saved my LoH for dire situations i.e.  your in guk and ya have a ton of adds and the chanter has agro and needs to still mez some mobs...... hit him with LoH just before he dies or your fighting and its getting messy and the cleric is about to die from having to cast that CH a little early LoH him you will be able to pick out the best person and best time to use your LoH and if you get LoH off while the health bar is purple you will get a grouping friend for life.... I have saved many of groups bacon with LoH and gained many friends with the good timing of LoH and have many healers demanding me in there groups when others still have the prejudice for pallys because of old rules because I have kept them alive and kept my cool and taken the death so others could get to the zone.... do the same and people will not forget who you are and you'll never go groupless<br> <br>Elohi<br> Loyal Knight of Mithaniel Marr<br><br>Yethuy<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 978<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/21/02 8:15:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice for a new paladin?</span><hr size=1> Just thought I'd mention, I'm level 11 now, and squire Narl for the testament of truth quest is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> green</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->!  How lame is that??  Now I gotta go pay some level 6 guy to help me out.  /weep<br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 339<br> <font color=#A